<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 98-12-10 - Assembling Two Piece (Articulated) Piston Used On the International&#174; 530 and 530E
        Engines Rated @ 300 HP and Above
    </stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi981210" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>98-12-10</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>June, 1998</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ENGINE</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Assembling Two Piece (Articulated) Piston Used On the International&#174; 530 and 530E Engines
                Rated @ 300 HP and Above
            </subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <engfamgroup/>

                <engfam>530</engfam>
                <engfam>530E</engfam>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The International&#174; 530 and 530E engines rated at 300 hp and above are equipped with two piece
                    (articulated) pistons. The top portion is the piston crown and the lower piece is the piston skirt.
                    A new articulated piston incorporating an offset pin hole was released starting with engine serial
                    number 1034668 for the International&#174; 530 and serial number 1027887 for the International&#174;
                    530E engines
                </para>
                <para>It is important that the new two piece piston is properly orientated when assembled. For assembly
                    alignment identification the piston crown has a nib (obstruction block) on one of the piston pin
                    bosses and the piston skirt has a raised triangle as part of the skirt casting. When assembling the
                    piston the raised formed triangle on the skirt and the piston pin boss side with the nib, on the
                    piston crown,
                    <emph type="bold">MUST BE</emph>
                    positioned (lined up) as shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9812101">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>If the piston skirt and crown are not assembled as described here piston slapping will
                            occur.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <para>The new piston crown and skirt will work for the old crown and skirt but, the new crown
                    <emph type="bold">CAN NOT</emph>
                    be used with the old skirt or vice versa. The new crown and skirt
                    <emph type="bold">MUST</emph>
                    be used together.
                </para>
                <figure id="f9812101" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g9812101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Aligning The Piston Skirt And Crown</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f9812101">Figure 1</hotlnk>, parts are upside down for assembling.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <para>For piston installation procedure refer to the engine service manual.</para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
